<TITLE> US help sought for 2nd Kaptai dam </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh has sought US assistance to build a second dam six kilometres downstream of the existing Kaptai hydroelectric dam to double power generation from the project. State minister for environment and forests Hasan Mahmud sought the assistance as Patrick S Moon, US deputy assistant secretary of state for south and central Asia, met him on Thursday at his secretariat office. Mahmud said: "The government is thinking of building the second dam in Kaptai lake and power plants there. It will double the power generation from the hydroelectricity project. We need US assistance for that." Public relations officer of the minister told bdnews24.com that the two sides discussed augmenting power generation by building dams on national rivers through regional cooperation. They also discussed furthering Bangladesh-US cooperation on environment-related issues, he said. Mahmud praised US president Barack Obama's role in the COP-15 in Copenhagen. Moon also hailed Bangladesh's role in leading the least developed countries at the conference. He said US would remain by Bangladesh government in its efforts to protect environmen
